The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 September is 72,432 (8,348.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 September, there were 1,815 new confirmed cases (209.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 September, there were 2,311 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 21% (496 fewer cases).
